# wetGDE Area Pipeline

Computes monthly wetGDE area (km¬≤) by WWF biome and country, either across a
full monthly time series or for a 12-month climatology. Output is written to
parquet.

---

## Structure

```
gde_area/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.py   # all paths, constants, logging setup
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ utils.py    # QA loading, masking, reprojection, pixel area, area summation
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ io.py       # biome/country rasterization, parquet save
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model.py    # orchestration and entry point
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
```

---

## Modes

Set `MODE` in `config.py` before running.

| `MODE` | Input | Time labels | Output time column |
|---|---|---|---|
| `"timeseries"` | Full monthly NetCDF | pandas Timestamps | `time` |
| `"climatology"` | 12-step mean annual cycle NetCDF | integers 1‚Äì12 | `month` |

Output filenames include the mode, e.g. `gde_area_by_biome_timeseries.parquet`.

---

## Configuration (`config.py`)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `MODE` | `"timeseries"` or `"climatology"` |
| `WET_NC` | Path to wetGDE NetCDF input |
| `BIOME_SHP` | Path to WWF terrestrial ecoregions shapefile |
| `COUNTRY_SHP` | Path to World Bank countries shapefile |
| `OPEN_WATER_TIF` | Path to GLWD open-water mask GeoTIFF |
| `PERSISTENCE_TIF` | Path to wetGDE persistence mask GeoTIFF |
| `QA_FILES` | List of QA flag NetCDF files (static flags + spin-up) |
| `OUT_DIR` | Output directory |
| `START_DATE` | Fallback start date for time axis decoding (timeseries mode only) |
| `MAX_WORKERS` | Number of threads for parallel area computation |
| `TEST_MODE` | If `True`, process only the first time step |

---

## Inputs

### wetGDE NetCDF (`WET_NC`)
- Variable name: `wetGDE`
- Dimensions: `(time, lat, lon)` or `(time, latitude, longitude)`
- For climatology mode: must have exactly 12 time steps

### QA flags (`QA_FILES`)
Two files are expected:
- `static_quality_flags.nc`: mountains, karst, and permafrost flags
- `spin_up_1960.nc`: spin-up quality flag

Cells are excluded where any static flag is non-zero, where spin-up flag is 4
or 6, or where open water is present.

### Persistence mask (`PERSISTENCE_TIF`)
Integer GeoTIFF with values:
- `-1` = nodata
- `0` = non-GDE
- `1` = episodic
- `2` = seasonal
- `3` = perennial

Only cells with values 1‚Äì3 are included in the analysis mask.

### Open-water mask (`OPEN_WATER_TIF`)
Binary GeoTIFF derived from GLWD. Cells flagged as open water are excluded.

### Shapefiles
- Biomes: WWF terrestrial ecoregions (`wwf_terr_ecos.shp`), field `BIOME`, values 1‚Äì14
- Countries: World Bank Admin0 10m, field `ISO`

---

## Outputs

Two parquet files per run:

### `gde_area_by_biome_{mode}.parquet`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `time` / `month` | Timestamp / int | Time label |
| `biome_id` | int | WWF biome ID (1‚Äì14) |
| `area_km2` | float | wetGDE area in km¬≤ |

### `gde_area_by_country_{mode}.parquet`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `time` / `month` | Timestamp / int | Time label |
| `ISO` | str | ISO country code |
| `area_km2` | float | wetGDE area in km¬≤ |

Country-time steps with zero wetGDE area are omitted.

---

## Running

```bash
# edit MODE and paths in config.py, then:
python model.py
```

Logs are written to both stdout and `OUT_DIR/gde_area_{mode}.log`.

---

## Analysis mask

The final analysis mask is the intersection of three conditions:

```
analysis_mask = qa_mask & spin_ok & (~open_water) & (persistence > 0)
```

This mask is static (time-invariant) and applied to every time step before
area computation.

